      "raw_text": "On hundred thousand dollars\nprofit on single piece of Spokane\nreal estate In one years time looks\ngood anywhere outside of Spo-\nkane. The Union Trust Co. has\nrejected an offer of this kind for\nits ground opposite the Paulsen\nbuilding on Riverside avenue, oc-\ncupied by one-story building fill\ned with railroad offices.\n\n\nJames c. Cunningham. secre-\ntary-treasurer of the Union Trust\nCo, told representative of The\nPress today that an offer of $780,\n900 cash had been made for this\ncorner by Il. j. Barney, the mil\nlionaire car builder of Dayton,"
